        "title": "Remove skill prelude exec allowlist",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Remove the `skillPrelude` exec allowlist compatibility path for `cat SKILL.md && printf ... && <skill-wrapper>` chains.\n- Keep direct trusted skill wrapper execution allowed while making old skill prelude chains go through normal approval flow.\n- Document that `autoAllowSkills` applies to real skill executables only and add a changelog entry.\n\nThis removes behavior introduced by https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/57839.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test -- src/infra/exec-approvals-analysis.test.ts src/agents/bash-tools.exec.approval-id.test.ts src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/infra/exec-approvals-allowlist.ts src/infra/exec-approvals-analysis.ts src/infra/exec-approvals-analysis.test.ts src/agents/bash-tools.exec.approval-id.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nKnown unrelated blocker in this checkout:\n\n- `pnpm tsgo:core:test` fails in OpenAI model test fixtures because `OpenAIModeModel` now requires `reasoning` and `OpenAICompletionsCompat` rejects `unsupportedToolSchemaKeywords`.\n- `pnpm changed:lanes --json` cannot run here because `origin/main...HEAD` has no merge base.\n",
